JOHANNESBURG - The DA says it’s time for Public Enterprises Minister Lynne Brown to leave office. This after the government announced the appointment of the new Eskom board. READ: Eskom appoints new board The government has ordered the new board to remove all Eskom executives who are facing allegations of corruption. “I think Minister Lynne Brown should be next, I’ve been saying that for some time now. Any minister that allowed Eskom to get to this level of ruin and to holding the country to ransom should step down. If she has any integrity she should do it immediately,” says Natasha Mazzone, DA Public Enterprises Spokesperson. eNCA